comments: White (SAS) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Jones (MEM) after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Forbes (SAS) slightly extends his forearm into Brooks (MEM), but does not dislodge him from his legally obtained position.
Aldridge briefly clamps the arm of Valanciunas (MEM), but does not affect his ability to defend in the post.
Valanciunas (MEM) extends his hand into Aldridge's (SAS) front and affects his SQBR.
Forbes (SAS) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Valanciunas (MEM) and absorbs the contact.
White (SAS) releases from Jones (MEM) as he slightly extends his forearm prior to the shot attempt, but does not dislodge Jones from his legally obtained position.
Aldridge (SAS) makes marginal contact with Crowder (MEM) that does not affect his ability to rebound.
Crowder (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Gay (SAS) and absorbs the contact.
Valanciunas (MEM) dislodges Aldridge (SAS) prior to receiving the pass in the post.
Valanciunas (MEM) and Aldridge (SAS) engage and disengage while rebounding.
White (SAS) makes clean contact to the ball during Valanciunas' (MEM) pass attempt.
Valanciunas (MEM) brings his arm down and makes contact to the head of DeRozan (SAS) on the driving shot attempt.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) steps out of bounds prior to releasing his shot attempt on the perimeter.
Aldridge (SAS) makes some contact to the arm Jackson Jr. (DET), but does not affect his control of the ball.
Gay (SAS) commits a take foul on Brooks (MEM).
Hill (MEM) places his arm to the front of DeRozan (SAS) at the start of the drive but the contact does not affect his SQBR.
Brooks (MEM) briefly places his hand to the opposite side hip of Aldridge (SAS), but does not affect his FOM.
Replay review of the foul called on Jackson Jr. (MEM) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful.
Aldridge (SAS) uses two hands to make contact to Crowder's (MEM) arms after he has secured the ball.  The contact occurs prior to the jump ball.
All technical fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
